Claims CLAIMS: 1. A computer- implemented method for generating optimized clinical data, the method comprising: acquiring (202) clinical data associated with one or more subjects, wherein the clinical data associated with a subject comprises a plurality of data sets each associated with a clinical attribute of the subject; acquiring (204) one or more clinical attribute criteria; selecting (206), for each of the one or more subjects, one or more data sets from the plurality of data sets based on the one or more clinical attribute criteria; and generating (208), for each of the selected one or more data sets, one or more statistical representations of the data set. 2. A computer-implemented method according to claim 1 , further comprising controlling a user interface to display the generated one or more statistical representations of each of the selected one or more data sets. 3. A computer-implemented method according to claim 2, wherein acquiring (202) the clinical data comprises acquiring clinical data associated with a plurality of subjects, and the method further comprises receiving a user selection of one of a cohort display mode and an individual display mode, wherein controlling the user interface comprises: controlling the user interface to display the generated one or more statistical representations of each of the selected data sets of the plurality of subjects, if the received user selection is the cohort display mode; and controlling the user interface to display the generated one or more statistical representations of each of the selected data sets of one of the plurality of subjects, if the received user selection in the individual display mode. 4. A computer- implemented method according to claim 3, wherein the generated one or more statistical representations of each of the selected one or more data sets is output in a scatter graph in the cohort display mode, and the generated one or more statistical 

 representations of each of the selected one or more data sets is output in a line graph in the individual display mode. 5. A computer-implemented method according to claim 3 or claim 4, further comprising: acquiring one or more personal attributes of each of the plurality of subjects; classifying each of the plurality of subjects into one of a plurality of subject subgroups based on a personal attribute of the subject; selecting a subject subgroup based on a user input; wherein generating one or more statistical representations comprises generating, for each of the plurality of subjects in the selected subject subgroup, one or more statistical representation of each of the selected one or more data sets. 6. A computer- implemented method according to claim 5, wherein the acquired one or more personal attributes is associated with at least one of an age of the subject and a gender of the subject. 7. A computer- implemented method according to any of claims 2 to 5, further comprising: receiving a user input to adjust an acquired clinical attribute criterion; adjusting the selection of one or more data sets based on the adjusted clinical attribute criterion; generating, for each of the adjusted selection of data sets, one or more statistical representations of the data set; and controlling the user interface to display the generated one or more statistical representations of the adjusted selection of data sets. 8. A computer-implemented method according to any of the preceding claims, wherein each of the plurality of data sets comprises a plurality of time series data values. 9. A computer-implemented method according to claim 8, wherein generating (208) the one or more statistical representation of the data set comprises calculating, based on the time series data values of the data set, at least one of: a nadir value, a maximum value, a mean value, a latest value, a number of time series data values in the data set, and a kernel- weighted value. 10. A computer- implemented method according to claim 8 or claim 9, wherein generating (208) the one or more statistical representation of the data set comprises calculating a kernel- weighted value of the time series data values based on a length of time between a time stamp of a respective time series data value and a reference time stamp. 11. A computer-implemented method according to any of claims 8 to 10, further comprising selecting, based on the acquired one or more clinical attribute criteria, a subgroup of time series data values for each of the selected one or more data sets, wherein generating (208) one or more statistical representations of the data set is based on the selected subgroup of time series data values in the selected data set. 12. A computer-implemented method according to any of the preceding claims, further comprising: acquiring a rule for calculating a user-derived value for a clinical attribute; and calculating, for each of the one or more subjects, the user-derived value for the clinical attribute based on the acquired rule and the clinical data associated with the subject. 13. A computer- implemented method according to any of the preceding claims, wherein the acquired one or more clinical attribute criteria is associated with at least one of: a clinical attribute, a target disease, one or more target subjects, a source of the clinical data, and a time period in which the clinical data is recorded. 14. A computer program product comprising a compute readable medium, the computer readable medium having computer readable code embodied therein, the computer readable code being configured such that , on execution by a suitable computer or processor, the computer or processor is caused to perform the method as claimed in any of claims 1 to 13. 15. An apparatus (100) for generating optimized clinical data, the apparatus comprising a processor (102) configured to: acquire clinical data associated with one or more subjects, wherein the clinical data associated with a subject comprises a plurality of data sets each associated with a clinical attribute of the subject; acquire one or more clinical attribute criteria; 

 select, for each of the one or more subjects, one or more data sets from the plurality of data sets based on the one or more clinical attribute criteria; and generate, for each of the selected one or more data sets, one or more statistical representations of the data set.
